snippet.textDisplay: @6:35 LOVE IT!! This is what Rutgers coach Greg Schiano been pushing for since 2011 after his DT Eric LeGrand was paralyzed after making a tackle during a kickoff. The NFL is floating the idea and it would be a GREAT change to the NFL. The kickoff now is a basically a roll of the dice, even if someone has a great return most of the time it is called back because of a block in the back or hold. BTW, the Average LOS after KO in 2019 was the 25.19 yard line, so option 1 is spot on.
